    <bodyBottom>
      <Value><![CDATA[<p>The unit is hosted within QMU’s Institute for Global Health and Development (IGHD). IGHD is recognised as a world leader in two major areas of research - health systems and mental health provision - and the work of the Unit brings together these two major strands.  </p>
<p>The unit’s work builds on ideas and methodologies developed in IGHD's previous work. This includes the study of post-conflict health systems recovery in Sierra Leone, Zimbabwe, Uganda and Cambodia, and also the resilience of health care systems in the Middle East, following the displacement of people from the conflict in Syria.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><img src="?width=300&amp;height=150" alt="American University of Belrut logo" width="300" height="150" data-udi="umb://media/10be45e422ee4eafba948ca628a2c33a"><img src="?width=300&amp;height=150" alt="RUHF logo" width="300" height="150" data-udi="umb://media/1a1ebe6d24c449b2815ccd1332ed2d9f"></p>
<p><img src="?width=300&amp;height=150" alt="COMAHS Logo" width="300" height="150" data-udi="umb://media/bd961efd28944ee18360f2186835ecdf"></p>]]></Value>
    </bodyBottom>
